author: kenanjeff
description:
Compositional Visual Genome (ComVG) 
ComVG benchmark aims to test vision-language models ability in text-to-image retrieval. 
We selected 542 high-quality images from Visual Genome and created 5400 datapoints in ComVG. 
Each datapoint contains a postive and negative image. The negative image is a mutated
variant with singular discrepancies in subject, object, or predicate.
For more details on creation process, please refer: https://arxiv.org/abs/2211.13854
